<?xml version="1.0"?>
<package xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
  <metadata>
    <id>calibre</id>
    <title>Calibre</title>
    <version>1.6.0</version>
    <authors>Kovid Goyal</authors>
    <owners>Gary Ewan Park</owners>
    <summary>calibre is the one stop solution to all your e-book needs.</summary>
    <description>calibre is a free and open source e-book library management application developed by users of e-books for users of e-books.</description>
    <projectUrl>http://calibre-ebook.com/</projectUrl>
    <tags>ebook library management</tags>
    <copyright>Kovid Goyal</copyright>
    <licenseUrl>http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl.html</licenseUrl>
    <requireLicenseAcceptance>false</requireLicenseAcceptance>
    <iconUrl>https://github.com/gep13/ChocolateyPackages/raw/master/calibre/calibre.ico</iconUrl>
    <releaseNotes>
    - New: Temporary marking of books in the library
    - New: Get Books: Add Wolne Lektury and Amazon (Canada) ebook stores
	- New: DOCX Input: Handle hyperlinks in footnotes and endnotes
	- New: Driver for Sunstech reader
	- New: Allow using both uri: and url: identifiers to create two different arbitrary links instead of just one in the Book details panel
	- New: E-book viewer: Make all keyboard shortcuts configurable
	- New: Conversion: Add an option to not condense CSS rules for margin, padding, border, etc. Option is under the Look & Feel section of the conversion dialog.
	- New: calibredb: Allow setting of title sort field
	- New: ebook-meta: Add an --identifier option to set identifiers.
	- Fixed: Fix a locking error when composite columns containing formats are used and formats are added and or deleted.
	- Fixed: EPUB Output: Do not strip object tags with type application svg xml in addition to those that use image svg xml.
	- Fixed: Cover grid: Fix selecting all books with Ctrl and A causing subsequent deselects to not fully work.
	- Fixed: HTMLZ Output: Fix long titles causing error when converting on windows.
	- Fixed: Content server: Fix OPDS category links to composite columns
	- Fixed: E-book viewer: Fix regression that broke import/export of bookmarks
	- Fixed: E-book viewer: Use the default font size setting for the dictionary view as well.
	- Fixed: DOCX Input: Avoid using the value attribute for simple numbered lists, to silence the asinine epubcheck
	- Fixed: HTML Input: Images linked by the poster attribute of the video tag are now recognized and processed.
	- Fixed: DOCX Input: Fix erorr when converting docx files that have numbering defined with no associated character style.
	- Fixed: EPUB Metadata: Implementing updating identifiers other than isbn in the epub file from calibre when polishing or exporting the epub
	- Fixed: Amazon metadata download: Fix parsing of some dates on amazon.de
	- New News Source: Various Uruguayan news sources by Carlos Alves
    - Improved News Source: National Geographic Magazine
	- Improved News Source: New York Review of Books
	- Improved News Source: Focus (PL)
	- Improved News Source: Carta Capital
	- Improved News Source: AM 730
	- Improved News Source: Ming Pao (HK)
	- Improved News Source: Neu Osnabrucker Zeitung
    </releaseNotes>
  </metadata>
</package>
